  "accepted_findings": [
    "The bounded component policy removes the V15 elongated off-crown ground carpets in both fixed corridor views.",
    "The source-masked 1,200-tree placement and near, mid, and runtime-far representation counts remain unchanged.",
    "Disabling mid and runtime-far leaf shadows prevents distant foliage cards from projecting broad valley-floor artifacts.",
    "The alpha2 no-shadow captures remain the best current corridor foliage reference and can support the next ecology expansion without changing saved material defaults."
  ],
  "rejection_reasons": [
    "Near-leaf dynamic shadows make affected crowns visually near-black and erase the olive color restored by RGB mip padding.",
    "Shadow-affected dark coverage rises to 36.26 percent in guide-seat and 42.17 percent in river-eye, while green classification falls below one percent.",
    "The candidate remains a sparse single-species line on smooth provisional terrain and is not a production forest treatment.",
    "No packaged desktop or on-device VR performance and temporal stability evidence exists for this shadow mode."
  ],
  "next_iteration_requirements": [
    "Keep leaf shadows disabled while adding the second ecology-reviewed native canopy stratum and denser source-masked forest bands.",
    "Revisit canopy shadows with a separately bounded shadow-pass density or simplified shadow proxy that preserves crown transmission and never changes collision or gameplay authority.",
    "Repeat the V15 off-crown artifact metric and crown photometry metric for every future shadow candidate.",
    "Do not promote alpha2 or any shadow mode until mixed ecology, moving-camera temporal stability, packaged desktop, and on-device VR gates pass."
  ]
